            <content>To make special provision to exempt certain persons from the obligation to be
                contributors under the Widows and Orphans Pension
                Ordinance.<marker role="blank-line"></marker><marker role="blank-line"></marker></content>
        </longTitle><commencementNote>[9 July 1976]</commencementNote><sourceNote>(Format changes—<ref href="/hk/2023/er2">E.R. 2 of 2023</ref>)</sourceNote><section id="ID_1438402829665_003" name="s1" reason="inEffect" startPeriod="1997-06-30" status="operational" temporalId="s1"><num value="1">1.</num><heading>Short title</heading><content>This Ordinance may be cited as the <shortTitle>Widows and Orphans Pension (Exemption) (Consolidation) Ordinance</shortTitle>.</content></section><section id="ID_1438402829681_002" name="s2" reason="inEffect" startPeriod="2023-05-25" status="operational" temporalId="s2"><num value="2">2.</num><heading>Exemption from obligation to contribute</heading><content>Notwithstanding the provisions of the Widows and Orphans Pension (Application)
            Regulations (<ref href="/hk/cap94A">Cap. 94 sub. leg. A</ref>), the term “officer” in
            the Widows and Orphans Pension Ordinance (<ref href="/hk/cap94">Cap. 94</ref>) shall not
            apply and shall be deemed never to have applied to the persons named in the <ref>First
                Schedule</ref>.</content><sourceNote>(Amended <ref href="/hk/2023/er2">E.R. 2 of 2023</ref>)</sourceNote></section><section id="ID_1438402829696_001" name="s3" reason="inEffect" startPeriod="1997-06-30" status="operational" temporalId="s3"><num value="3">3.</num><heading>Refund of contributions</heading><content>All contributions made by the persons named in the <ref>Second Schedule</ref> under the Widows and Orphans Pension Ordinance (<ref href="/hk/cap94">Cap. 94</ref>) shall be refunded to them.</content></section><schedule id="ID_1438402829696_003" name="sch1" reason="inEffect" startPeriod="2023-05-25" status="operational" temporalId="sch1"><num value="1">First
